<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100014441195185></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100014441195185><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=100014441195185>SUNSTRKE != CRAP</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=100014441195185#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Sep 10th 1:53 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>1) All DD spells must be cold, fire, or magic based. At the level you're going to use it, all mobs will probably have good cold, fire, and magic resist. The solution is to have debuffers who can lower resists (via malise, bard debuff songs, tashi, etc.).<br><br>2) IC does 1120 max damage for 400 mana, a dmg:mana ratio of 2.8. Sunstrike does 1615 damage for 450 mana, a dmg:mana ratio of about 3.59 (rounding up from 3.5888888888...). <br><br>3) The cycle time on IC is 8.8 seconds (6.3 cast time + 2.5 recast time). The cycle time on Sunstrike is 7 seconds (7.0 cast + 0.0 recast).<br><br>4) Neither IC or Sunstrike are "fast damage" spells. That's what draughts are for. If you don't believe me, look at the damage/second output of the 51 draught: at max damage it does 229.3 damage/sec, and IC does 160 - Draught of Ice (57) does 243.6 damage/sec at max damage, SS does 230.7. These spells are "kill shot" spells, used when you need to deal one LARGE blow to the enemy. It's unlikely you would open a fight with either spell, as you would aggro the heck out of the mob and promptly be smashed into a pulp.<br><br>5) There already are two spells that do 2000 points of damage, the special purpose wrath spells which are used against giant and dragon mobs in Velious (meaning that VI probably won't make another 2000 point DD spell for use against all mobs).<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
