	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, I'm a lvl 20 DE Wizard. First, this was my wife's character and after a while (at lvl 6), she got bored and quit. I took her up and played awhile. Found out this little girl is one hell of a nuker, whether in a group or solo'g. I found some frustation in the mid teen lvl's. Knowing I would get to the next lvl slowly, I just trugged onward. Quit looking at the lvl bar and BAM, "You have raised your Level". Being a DE, I fought in Neriak until lvl 10, hunting everything that moved and was blue. My root spell I do not trust that much and with little mana for good reasons. From 10-14, I grouped or solo'd in NRO and finally headed down to Oasis until lvl 20. Now that I got my personal gate spells, I'm ready for my next adventure. Yeah, some lvls are slower than others but I'm in no hurry and I could use all the cash I can get my little dark hands on. The only advise I can give is when you think its boring and slow, just sit back, don't be in a hurry and practice your skills. Of all the lvls, 19 was the slowest, maybe because I wanted to be a 20 quicker than I thought, but after dying a few times and looking at my lvl bar.. Hell, I wanted to cry some, but held my head up high and spoke of revenge and by damn, I made it. <br>Lailial<br>20th season Wizardress<br>Tradewind Walkers -&gt; Officer<br>Innoruuk<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
